Sokoto State Governor, Alhaji Aminu Waziri Tambuwal has called on the newly elected Speaker of the Kaduna State House of Assembly to always think of Kaduna state first and practice politics without bitterness. He made this call during a courtesy visit to the Kaduna state assembly speaker, Rt. Hon. Yusuf Ibrahim Zailani on Monday. The Sokoto state governor said the purpose of his visit to Kaduna state was to sympathise with governor El-rufai over the recent killings which occurred in some part of kaduna state and secondly to congratulate the newly elected Kaduna speaker, Hon. Yusuf Ibrahim Zailani on his becoming the Kaduna speaker. “Whenever election is over, then politics without bitterness is what every politician should embrace so as to move the state forward in terms of peaceful coexistence and development. “For instance in Sokoto state, the speaker is from the APC, but we have always worked together because we have the interest of the masses at heart.” He said. “I urge Zailani to always think of Kaduna state first and then he should make sure he brings his members together so as to achieve their purpose of being elected for dividend of democracy to be enjoyed by the people who elected them” He said. Tambuwal also called on the members of the Kaduna assembly to always support the speaker so that every promise made to the people of the state is delivered. 